benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Retrieve bundle custom fields

covered: Valid Request: Successful 200 responses with correct JSON array and schema (TC01–TC03, TC10–TC12, TC14, TC15, TC19).
Empty Response: 200 with empty array when no custom fields exist (TC04).
Query Parameters: Default audit (NONE) and valid values FULL/MINIMAL covered; invalid/partial values rejected; unexpected params ignored (TC01–TC03, TC07, TC10, TC13).
Error Handling: 400 for invalid bundleId format and injection attempts; 404 for not found; 503 for backend/audit service outages (TC05, TC06, TC09, TC16, TC17, TC18).
Content-Type/Produces: application/json verified and body is valid JSON (TC20).
Security/Robustness: SQL injection and XSS attempts handled (TC17, TC18).
Boundary/Volume: One, maximum, and large-number performance considered (TC11, TC12, TC14).
gaps: Rate Limiting: No explicit tests for throttling behavior (e.g., 429 Too Many Requests) or X-RateLimit headers; concurrency (TC19) does not validate rate-limit semantics.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios verifying ETag/If-None-Match, Last-Modified/If-Modified-Since, Cache-Control, or 304 Not Modified responses.
Authorization vs Authentication: No 403 Forbidden scenario for insufficient privileges/roles if applicable to this endpoint.
Content Negotiation: No tests for Accept header handling or 406 Not Acceptable when an unsupported media type is requested.
Audit Parameter Robustness: No cases for case sensitivity (e.g., audit=full vs FULL) or leading/trailing whitespace handling; expected behavior not asserted.
recommendations: Add rate limiting tests: burst requests leading to 429, and validate presence/values of X-RateLimit-* headers when applicable.
Add caching tests: verify Cache-Control and ETag/Last-Modified in 200; send conditional GET with If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since and expect 304 when unchanged.
Add a 403 Forbidden scenario for users lacking required roles/permissions (distinct from missing/invalid token).
Add content negotiation tests: request with Accept: application/json (200) and an unsupported Accept (e.g., text/xml) expecting 406.
Expand audit parameter tests for input normalization: audit=full (case), audit=' FULL ' (whitespace) to assert either acceptance (normalized) or 400 per spec.
Optionally assert the CustomField schema more strictly: required fields, data types, and no additional unexpected properties.
